{
  "texts": [
    "Since P is closed under intersection, P ′ is clearly closed under intersection as well.",
    "For the other two closure conditions, suppose X ′ ∈ P ′, so there is an X ∈ P such thatX ′ = min⟨S, ⊑⟩ ∩ X.",
    "Since X ∈ P, it follows by Definition 2.1 and Re- mark 2.15 that int(S \\ X) = {x ∈ S | ↓x ∩ X = ∅} ∈ P. Now we claim that S ′ \\ X ′ = min⟨S, ⊑⟩ ∩ int(S \\ X).",
    "For the right-to-left inclusion, if a ∈ min⟨S, ⊑⟩ ∩ int(S \\ X), then from a ∈ min⟨S, ⊑⟩ we have a ∈ S ′ and from a ∈ int(S \\ X) we have a ̸ ∈ X, so a ̸ ∈ X ′.",
    "From left to right, if a ∈ S ′ \\ X ′, then a ∈ min⟨S, ⊑⟩ but a ̸ ∈ X,which together imply a ∈ int(S \\ X), so a ∈ min⟨S, ⊑⟩ ∩ int(S \\ X)."
  ]
}